To run VE programs you need the following environment variables set

VEROOT ~ivy/ve-2.2
LD_LIBRARY_PATH ~ivy/ve-2.2/lib

Try running the program in this directory

./3dsviewer.linux newbeetle newbeetle.3ds

You should have a window with a red and white checkerboard and part of a beetle showing. The
following keyboard commands are understood (cursor must be on the window)

s/S - scale the object
x/X - translate the object in x
y/Y - translate the object in y
z/Z - translate the object in z
p/P - rotate the object
q/Q - rotate the object
t/T - rotate the object
a/d - move forward and backwards
arrow keys move you as well.

You should be able to copy this program and run it anywhere.

